text.tspan: *VUSB and VIN are electrically connected; they can be isolated by cutting JP1.
WARNING: Do not connect a voltage source to VIN if Empyrean is already
connected to USB! If you do, the host and/or Empyrean will likely be damaged!

path.style: font-style:italic;-inkscape-font-specification:'DIN 1451 Engschrift Italic'

text.tspan: *8 kB flash storage reserved for bootloader
5 VDC regulated (from USB or on VUSB pin)
The most common option for powering
Empyrean is via the USB port. The on-board
voltage regulator provides 3.3 V to the
microcontroller from the 5 V USB bus. You may
provide your own 5 V regulated supply to the
VUSB pin if the board is not connected to USB.
Empyrean can also accept a 5-16 V power supply
on the VIN pin (see important note below).
Finally, you may supply 3.3 V regulated to the
3.3V pin if the board is to be used stand-alone
Connects 5V USB bus to Empyrean VIN
regulator). Cut jumper to use an
Cut jumper to disable the red power LED.
Empyrean comes with a bootloader preinstalled for easy Arduino
sketch loading. You may load a sketch onto Empyrean by either
using the Arduino IDE upload function or by mounting Empyrean
on your PC as a storage device with a quick double-press of the
RESET button and dragging a sketch in UF2 format to the window.
Single press: Reset and execute sketch
